sentences: Noon is a pseudonym of Polish electronic musician and producer Mikołaj Bugajak.
He was born in 1979 in Warsaw, Poland.
He began his career with the hip-hop band Grammatik, which in 1998 issued its first EP.
All of Noon’s works are based on vinyl sampling and spiced up with analogue synthesis.
Noon's tracks also appeared on UK based Canteen Records and Canadian Launchbox Recordings labels' releases.
Studio Games (Gry Studyjne) (2003, Teeto Records/Canteen Records)
